        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:228:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/360/445",
        "text": [
          "۳۶۰. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): لَا تَظُنَّنَّ بِكَلِمَةٍ خَرَجَتْ مِنْ أَحَدٍ سَوءاً، وَأَنْتَ تَجِدُ لَهَا فِي الْخَيْرِ مُحْتَمَلاً."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "360. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: Do not regard an expression uttered by any person as evil if you can find it capable of bearing some good."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
